  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In a prospective study the investigators perform repeated cholangioscopies in all patients
      that received percutaneous transhepatic biliary drainage (PTBD) for a variety of malignant
      and benign diseases. Endoscopic findings and their correlation with clinical features will be
      recorded prospectively. The impact on clinical decision will be evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
